result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler T. Myers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyler T. Myers is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyler T. Myers was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:50 AM DA calls cases: 22CF46, 22TR240 and states appearances. Defendant Tyler T. Myers in court.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states an agreement has been reached in this matter and recites the agreement on record. Contingent upon the defendant's plea to Ct. 2 in case 22CF46 the State will move to dismiss Ct. 1. So ordered. In case 22TR240 the defendant will plead to the sole charge in this matter and the State will move to amend the charge to 1-10 over. So ordered. Court questions the defendant on counsel. Defendant states he would like to obtain counsel before proceeding. Notice of right to attorney given to Defendant. Defendant decides to move forward without an Attorney. Defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives the right to an attorney. DE enters plea of GUILTY to count 2 in case 22CF46 and to Ct. 1 in case 22TR240 therefore Ct. 1 in case 22CF46 is DISMISSED. Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC. Comments by parties. 
22CF46-
Ct. 1- Dismissed
Ct. 2- 
$330 Fine 
$200 DNA + Sample
Defendant is given 9 days Sentence Credit 

22TR240- 
$175.30 Forfeiture

Monetary obligations: 30 days to pay or one day in jail for every $25.00 then owing, until paid in full. 


Appeal Rights Given
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 9, 2022 at 10:00 am.

10:10 AM Defendant Tyler T Myers appeared in court. Karl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  Notice of right to attorney given to DE. Bond already set and is to continue. Preliminary hearing requested, time limits waived.   Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.
State's demand for discovery and notice of intent to use DNA evidence
DE not operate a motor vehicle unless he/she has a valid dl in their possession.

2:08 PM DA calls case and states appearances and possible charges. Defendant appeared via video from Price County Jail. Krl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DE next court date is  4/12/22 at 10 am.  Jail gives DE a notice of right to attorney.  Court questions parties as to bond.  DA states bond recommendation. Bond ordered as requested.
